  "prompt": "What are some tips and hacks for bench press?",
  "response": "Here are some tips and hacks for improving your bench press:\n\n1. Technique Tips:\n- Keep your feet firmly planted\n- Maintain a slight arch in your lower back\n- Keep your shoulders retracted and chest up\n- Take a tight grip slightly wider than shoulder-width\n- Lower the bar to mid-chest, not upper chest\n- Breathe in on descent, exhale while pressing\n\n2. Strength/Performance Hacks:\n- Use leg drive to generate more power\n- Practice pause reps to improve strength\n- Incorporate progressive overload\n- Train triceps and shoulders for supporting muscles\n- Use proper warm-up sets\n- Vary your grip width\n\n3. Setup Tricks:\n- Use a consistent unracking technique\n- Position yourself symmetrically on the bench\n- Squeeze the bar tightly\n- Keep wrists straight and aligned\n\n4. Equipment/Safety:\n- Use a spotter for heavy lifts\n- Wear wrist wraps for support\n- Use proper weight lifting shoes\n- Consider using a lifting belt\n\n5. Accessory Exercises:\n- Do close-grip bench press\n- Practice dumbbell bench press\n- Include push-ups and dips\n- Do tricep extensions\n\nRemember to focus on proper form and gradual progression.",
